* PANJIT SVT15100UB -- 100V 15A Extreme-Low-VF Trench-MOS Schottky (TO-277B)
* Datasheet SVT15100UB-REV.02 (2025-12-10). No vendor SPICE model published
* (Panjit's library has no SVT/trench parts) -- this is a datasheet fit.
* Built with the same method as ST15100S (see spice-fit/svt15100ub/): table
* anchors + gridline-digitized Fig-4 (four temp curves) & Fig-2 cap, scipy fit,
* LTspice-validated. See the datasheet-over-vendor-model note in the repo.
*
* Lower-VF, lower-leakage alternative to SMC ST15100S (0.61 vs 0.68 V @15A typ).
*
* VALIDATED in LTspice (spice-fit/svt15100ub/):
*   VF @15A : 25C = 0.608 V (datasheet typ 0.61 / max 0.66)
*            125C = 0.529 V (datasheet Fig-4 ~0.54; table gives only 1A/5A @125C)
*   VF @5A/1A, 25C = 0.474/0.389 V (table 0.47/0.38)
*   Cap CJ  : ~2019/1091/707 pF @ 1/5/10 V (datasheet Fig-2 ~2000/1250/600)
* Fit optimised for the 1-20A operating region; the single-junction cap model
* can't perfectly track Fig-2's flat-then-knee shape (MJ=0.90 is the compromise).
*
* TRS1=0 (datasheet incremental R ~14mOhm at BOTH 25C & 125C, 5->15A -> RS is
* temp-independent), so the 25/125C curves do NOT cross at high current (gap
* stays ~75mV) -- physical, avoiding the vendor-model failure mode where an
* over-large RS tempco makes the hot curve explode past the cold one.
* EG=0.65 (~Schottky barrier) reproduces the forward VF(T) shift across all four
* datasheet curves (25/75/125/150 C) and the ~1000x reverse-leakage temp ratio
* (80uA@25C -> 15mA@125C at 100V). TT=0: Schottky, negligible reverse recovery.
* CAVEAT: reverse-leakage magnitude ~10x low (single-diode Schottky limit).
*
.MODEL SVT15100UB D (
+ LEVEL=1 IS=9.5e-7 N=1.05 RS=0.0104
+ BV=110 IBV=1e-4
+ CJO=2.6n VJ=3.08 MJ=0.90 FC=0.5
+ TT=0 EG=0.651 XTI=1.17 TRS1=0 )
